column5: Laureate head of bearded Heracles, left club behind.","Zeus standing facing, head left, naked to waist, holding patera in outstretched right hand, left resting on sceptre at his feet, eagle, standing left, head right, with half spread wings.
column6: "Bearded Heracles, adorned with laurel wreath on his head, with a club positioned behind him on the left,", "Zeus stands in a forward stance, his head turned left, bare until the waist, a patera held high in his right hand, his left hand comfortably resting on a sceptre at his feet, an eagle stands to his left, its head turned right, wings semi-spread."
column7: "Bearded Heracles with a laureate head, a club is placed behind to the left. Zeus, partially naked to the waist, is standing and facing with his head oriented towards the left. He extends his right hand, holding a patera, while his left hand rests on a sceptre positioned at his feet. An eagle, positioned to his left, gazes to the right with its wings half spread."
column8: "Head of Heracles with laurel, bearded, and a club situated behind, to the left. Zeus is positioned upright with his head to the left, unclothed from the waist up, bearing a patera in his extended right hand and the left resting on a sceptre. At his feet is an eagle, standing to the left but its head facing right, wings partially unfurled."
column9: "A laurel-wreathed depiction of a bearded Hercules with a club placed behind him on the left side," "A half-bared torso portrait of Zeus facing forward, his head turning to the left, with a patera held out in his right hand while his left hand is resting on a sceptre. An eagle with partially extended wings stands to his feet, its position facing left but its head looking rightwards."
column10: "Crowned portrait of whiskered Heracles, with a club to the rear on his left," "Zeus in a standing posture facing frontward, his head turned left, bare-chested, carrying a patera using his extended right hand and his left supporting a sceptre. At his foot lies an eagle looking to the right with partially spread wings."
column11: "Crowned portrait of a bearded Heracles, featuring a club behind to the left," "A bare-chested Zeus in a standing position facing forward, with his head turned to the left, holding a patera in his extended right hand, his left placed on a sceptre at his feet, and an eagle close by, standing on his left side, with its head turned to its right, having semi-extended wings."
column12: "Crowned depiction of a bearded Hercules, with a club positioned behind him. Zeus, depicted semi-nude to the midriff, stands in a forward facing position but with his head turned to the left. He holds a patera in his extended right hand, while his left hand leans on a sceptre placed close to his feet. An eagle, standing on his left, is shown with its head turned rightwards, presenting half-opened wings."
column13: "Bearded Heracles with a laureate crown, with a club positioned behind him to the left. Zeus, bare to the waist and positioned to face the viewer, his head turned to the left. He extends his right hand, a patera held within, while his left hand rests upon a sceptre at his feet. An eagle with semi-opened wings stands at his feet to the left, its head facing right."
column14: "This historical coin features the crowned figure of a bearded Heracles, with his club depicted behind. On the reverse, Zeus is portrayed standing and facing forward, his head turned to the left. He is uncovered from the waist up, bearing a patera in his extended right hand, and his left hand is positioned on a sceptre. An eagle, head turned to the right and wings partially spread, is situated at his feet."
column15: "A crowned portrait of a bearded Hercules with a club behind the left side. An image of Zeus, partially undressed upper body, in a standing position, facing forward with his head turned left. Zeus is depicted holding a patera, a ceremonial dish, in his raised right hand whilst his left hand remains rested on a scepter at his feet. Accompanying Zeus is an eagle, standing to his left side with a right-directed head and half spread wings."

column5: Head of (youthful) Dionysus, right, wearing taenia and ivy wreath with five leaves and two fruits. Hair dress rolled in the back and with two curls falling on his back.","Nude Heracles standing facing, head left, resting right hand on club, left hand on hip, holding lion skin in left arm.
column6: "Depicted on the front is a young Dionysus facing to the right, donned with a taenia and an ivy crown featuring five leaves and a pair of fruits. His hairstyle comprises a roll at the back with two locks cascading down onto his back. On the flip, a sans-clothing Heracles can be seen in a standing position, his gaze directed to the left. He supports his right hand on his club, left hand placed on his waist, with the skin of a lion draped over his left arm."
column7: "Portrait of a youthful Dionysus facing right, adorned with a taenia and an ivy crown comprising of five leaves and a pair of fruits. His hair is styled in a roll at the back with two loose curls cascading down his back.", "Heracles, in the nude, stands imposingly, gazing leftwards, with his right hand relaxed on his club and his left hand resting on his waist, draping the lion's skin over his left arm."
column8: The image on the coin depicts a youthful Dionysus facing in the right direction. He is adorned with a taenia and an ivy wreath that consists of five leaves and two fruits. His hairstyle features even rolls at the back of his head with two curls cascading down his back. On the reverse side of the coin, we see a bare Heracles. He is standing upright, his head turned to the left. He nonchalantly rests his right hand on a club, with his left hand positioned on his hip, and carrying a lion's skin in his left arm.
column9: "Depicted on the coin is a young Dionysus, his head turned to the right, adorned with a taenia and an ivy wreath garnished with five leaves and a pair of fruits. His hair is fashioned in a roll at the back and two loose curls fall onto his back. On the flip side of the coin, we see a bare Heracles in a standing position, his face veered to the left, his right hand resting on a club, left hand perched on his hip while cradling a lion's skin in his left arm."
column10: Depiction of a youthful Dionysus on the front, directed to the right, adorned with a taenia and a wreath of ivy featuring five leaves and a pair of fruits. His hair is arranged in a roll at the back with two ringlets cascading down his back. Conversely, on the other side, a bare Heracles is presented standing face-on but looking to the left, with his right hand leaning on a club. His left hand is placed on his waist, draping the lion skin over his left arm.
column11: "This coin features an image of a young Dionysus, facing right, adorned with a wreath of ivy, filled with five leaves, and two pieces of fruit. His hair is styled in a roll at the back, with a pair of curls cascading down onto his back. On the flip side, Heracles is depicted standing nude, oriented forward but with his head turned to the left. His right hand rests on his club, while his left hand sits on his hip. The skin of a lion is draped over his left arm."
column12: This is an alternate description of a historical coin: "The face depicts a young Dionysus, oriented to the right, garbed in a taenia and an ivy wreath adorned with five leaves and a pair of fruits. His hairstyle features a roll at the back with two cascading curls down his back." "On the reverse side, we find a bare Heracles, shown in a frontal position, his head turned left. His right hand rests on his club, while his left hand strikes a pose on his hip, holding a lion's skin draped over his left arm."
column13: "Depiction of a young Dionysus on the head side, looking to the right, adorned with a taenia and an ivy crown consisting of five leaves and two fruits. His hairstyle is elegantly rolled at the back with two loose curls cascading down his back." "On the flip side, a bare Hercules is standing upright facing forward, with his head turned to the left. His right hand leisurely rests on his club, as his left hand is positioned on his hip. He carries a lion's skin draped over his left arm."
column14: This is a depiction of an ancient coin: "A young Dionysus' portrait facing right adorns the surface, embellished with a band, also known as taenia, and an ivy circlet consisting of five leaves and a couple of fruits. His hairstyle is fashioned into a roll in the back, with two strands loosely hanging on his back," and "A bare Heracles stands front and center, looking left, with his right hand casually resting on a club and his left holding his hip, while deftly clutching a lion's pelt with his left arm."
column15: The coin displays a portrait of a young Dionysus on the right, adorned with a taenia and an ivy wreath composed of five leaves and two fruits. His hairstyle is rolled up at the back, with two cascading curls falling onto his back. On the flip side, a bare Heracles is depicted standing frontally, with his head turned to the left. His right hand rests on a club, with his left hand on his waist, while he drapes a lion's skin over his left arm.

column5: Head of Kore Soteira left with her hair tied up in a shawl (sakkos), ears of grain, and an earring below the neck a tunny left.","Apollo with laurel wreath sitting left on the omphalos covered with woolen bandages and standing on a base, turning his naked torso forward in his outstretched right hand a patera or plectrum, his left arm resting on a cithara.
column6: This historical coin features the likeness of Kore Soteira, her head turned to the left, with her hair neatly tucked in a shawl, or sakkos. An earring can be noticed beneath her neck, accompanied by symbols of grain ears and a tunny positioned to her left. Flipping the coin, one can find a depiction of Apollo, donning a laurel wreath and seated on the omphalos, which is adorned with woolen wraps. He is placed on a base, his bare torso twists forward as his right hand extends holding a patera or plectrum, while his left arm is casually placed on a cithara.
column7: "The obverse of the coin features Kore Soteira's visage with her coiffure wrapped in a sakkos, embellished with grain ears and a dangling earring beneath her neck, and a depiction of a tunny to her left. The reverse displays Apollo, donned with a laurel wreath, positioned on the omphalos, which is swathed in woolen wraps and set on a pedestal. He is viewed from the side with his bare torso twisted to the front. In his extended right hand, he holds either a patera or plectrum, while his left arm leans on a cithara."
column8: This is an alternative depiction of a historic coin: "A left-facing image of Kore Soteira with her hair neatly tied in a shawl (sakkos), complemented by ears of grain and an earring just below her neck which features a tunny to the left." "Apollo, donning a laurel wreath, is seated on the left on an omphalos that is cloaked in woolen wrappings and elevated on a platform. His nude torso is forward-turned, his right hand extending to hold either a patera or plectrum, his left arm comfortably leans on a cithara."
column9: "Left-facing depiction of Kore Soteira, hair neatly encased in a sakkos, with grain sheaves and an earring beneath her neck, and a tunny fish to the left. Apollo, donned with a laurel wreath, is seated on a wool-covered omphalos with a base, his nude upper body swiveling forwards. He is seen holding either a patera or a plectrum in his outstretched right hand, while his left arm provides rest for a cithara."
column10: "The profile of Kore Soteira can be seen on the left with her hair bundled up in a shawl (sakkos), featuring ears of grain and an earring located just below her neck. This is accompanied by the image of a tunny fish in her direction of gaze.","Subsequently, Apollo is illustrated while sitting on the left on the omphalos that is covered with bandages made of wool, and is positioned on a base. His bare torso is oriented forwards. In his right hand, extended outwards, he holds either a patera or plectrum. His left arm finds rest on a cithara."
column11: "An illustration of Kore Soteira is featured on the left with her hair gracefully arranged in a shawl, also known as a sakkos. Ears of grain and an earring are depicted below her neck, to her left is a tunny. On the other side, Apollo is portrayed adorned with a laurel wreath, seated to the left on the omphalos, which is swathed in wool. He is positioned on a base with his bare torso turned forward. In his outwardly extended right hand he holds a patera or plectrum, while his left arm finds rest on a cithara."
column12: "This coin features the visage of Kore Soteira, her hair artfully arranged within a shawl (sakkos), garnished by ears of grain, and an earring subtly placed below the neck. A tunny, illustrated left, completes her portrayal." The flip side of the coin introduces Apollo, adorned with a laurel wreath, gracefully seated on the omphalos that's elegantly covered in woolen wraps, and stationed on a base. His nude torso is turned forward as he extends his right hand holding a patera or plectrum, while his left arm languidly rests on a cithara."
column13: "Kore Soteira's profile to the left, her hair secured in a shawl (sakkos), wheat stems present, and an ornamental earring beneath her neck, with a tunny fish facing to the left.","Apollo featuring a laurel wreath seated on the left side atop the omphalos, which is wrapped in wool bandages, his naked upper body twisted at the front, in his stretched-out right hand, he holds either a patera or a plectrum, his left arm leisurely leaning on a cithara."
column14: "This coin features the image of Kore Soteira with her hair wrapped in a kerchief, embellished with wheat stems, and an earring peeping out below her neck, graced with a left-facing tunny fish. On the reverse, Apollo dons a laurel wreath, poised to the left on a wool-wrapped omphalos standing on a pedestal.
